This paper deals with the semantics of logic programming, which is a subfield of both logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of categories and coalgebras, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and category theory (math.CT). Finally, the paper touches on the relationship between logic programming and software engineering (cs.SE), as it discusses the proof-search aspect of logic programming. Overall, cs.LO and cs.PL are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.SE.
